<p>I'm following an introduction to Computer Science using Scheme. I am into the following problem, and I come up with a solution, it seems however that I'm lost in the syntax.</p>  <p>Define a procedure last-pair that returns the list that contains only the last element of a given (nonempty) list: (last-pair (list 23 72 149 34))</p>  <p>Here is my solution:</p>  <pre><code>   (define (last-pair array)       ((define (get-last (length array) array))         (if (= (length array) 1) (car array)          (get-last (- 1 (length array)) (cdr array)))))) </code></pre>  <p>Here is the mistake: Error: Invalid lambda: (lambda ((length array) array))</p>